# HAP dashboards — C-suite improvement loop (340B + OW + print + shared)

Cursor should behave as a **structured improvement partner**: propose high-impact changes, **never invent data or policy**, and assume **humans merge/deploy**.

## Non-negotiables

- **Accuracy:** All numbers, dates, and law references must match `state-data.js`, report copy, and cited sources. If unsure, flag—do not guess.
- **Security:** Follow `SECURE-FORCE.md` / project security rules: safe DOM, no secrets, validated hash/state, IT-safe rules for `340b-BASIC.html`.
- **Cross-surface impact:** Edits to `340b.css`, `hap-design-tokens.css`, `hap-nav-shared.js`, or shared copy patterns can affect **340B advanced, BASIC, OW (`OW_report_dashboard.html`), index/static, print**. Call out blast radius before large changes.

## Recommended heading hierarchy (use consistently)

| Level | Role | Notes |
|-------|------|--------|
| **H1** | Page purpose (one per page) | Dashboard title / report title. |
| **H2** | Major sections | Overview, Key metrics, Map, HAP position, Community impact, Sources. |
| **H3** | Subsections or card groups | “What lawmakers can do”, metric groups, methodology blocks. |
| **H4** | Bullets / advocacy lines / stat labels | Pair with one-line “Why it matters” where space allows. |

**HAP Position:** treat as its **own** H2 band (full-width flagship under Overview): eyebrow → headline pledge → short lead → H3 “What lawmakers can do” → H4-style bullets with “Why it matters”.

## Copy defaults

- **Reading level:** Plain English; short sentences; **8th–10th grade** where possible.
- **Why it matters:** One line under or beside every stat, advocacy bullet, and primary CTA explaining impact for patients, hospitals, or policy.
- **Acronyms:** Define **340B, PBM, contract pharmacy** once per page (glossary strip on 340B); OW uses PA hospital/sustainability language—do not paste unrelated 340B stats onto OW.
- **Dates:** Prefer “Data as of [month year]” near KPI blocks; align with `CONFIG` / `state-data.js`.

## Visual & design cohesion

- **Tokens:** Prefer `hap-design-tokens.css` variables (`--hap-brand-primary`, `--hap-type-h*`, spacing) before new hex values.
- **Oliver Wyman–style surfaces:** Light, clean backgrounds; **airy** section rhythm; separate bands with **spacing + subtle background shifts**—avoid heavy/dark UI blocks unless contrast is required for a11y.
- **Strict semantic colors (no random hex):** Use suite tokens only:
  | Role | Token family | Meaning |
  |------|----------------|---------|
  | **Green** | `--hap-topic-finance*` | Financial / savings / funding |
  | **Blue** | `--hap-topic-access*` | Coverage / insurance / access |
  | **Purple** | `--hap-topic-policy*` | Policy / regulation / legal context |
  | **Orange** | `--hap-topic-risk*` | Risk / pressure / constraints |
  | **Neutral** | `--hap-topic-neutral*` | Supporting info |
  | **Direction** | `--hap-sentiment-positive*` / `--hap-sentiment-negative*` | Cool = gains/stability; warm = loss/restriction (never rely on color alone) |
- **Executive KPIs (“big number” standard):** Large dominant value + short label + one-line **Impact** or **Why it matters** (professional briefing language). Prefer opt-in pattern `.hap-kpi-executive` + `.hap-kpi-value` / `.hap-kpi-label` / `.hap-kpi-meaning` from `hap-design-tokens.css`; tune per card with topic tokens for accents only.
- **Flagship rows:** Overview → **HAP Position** (full-width, HAP-branded band) → key findings / metrics; consistent card padding (`--space-*`, `--radius-*`).
- **Polish:** Subtle borders/shadows from tokens; HAP blue for primary brand moments; avoid loud gradients on dense data screens.

## UX & interactivity

- **Maps:** Preserve failure isolation (map issues must not break print/share). Tooltips via `title` or existing tooltip elements—no `innerHTML` with raw user input.
- **Motion:** Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; prefer `transform`/`opacity` for hovers.
- **Targets:** Interactive controls ≥ **44px** where practical (nav pills, primary actions).

## Performance

- Avoid layout thrashing: batch DOM reads/writes; keep scroll handlers **passive** + **rAF** where already used in `340b.js`.
- Do not add heavy always-on observers without need; prefer CSS for hover/focus states.

## Shared-code risks (review when touching)

- **`340b.html` inlined `CONFIG` vs `state-data.js`:** duplicated; updates must stay in sync or drift.
- **`hap-nav-shared.js`:** section IDs must exist on the page; scroll-margin must match header height.
- **OW inline `<style>` vs `340b.css`:** OW does not load full `340b.css`; token file is linked—keep OW variables aligned with tokens.
- **Print pipeline:** `print.html` / `print-view.css` / `340b.js` print snapshot—changes to intro/HAP DOM affect PDF first page.

## Improvement loop (human-controlled)

1. **Analyze** — Copy, hierarchy, semantic colors, a11y, cross-dashboard drift (340B, BASIC, OW/index/static, print, shared nav).
2. **Propose** — Ranked by impact vs effort; call out blast radius (`340b.css`, tokens, `hap-nav-shared.js`, print pipeline).
3. **Implement** — **Human approval before large merges**; default to **small, high-impact diffs** (no bulk rewrites unless scoped).
4. **Verify** — `python3 dashboard-audit.py`; spot-check print/PDF; hash navigation; BASIC IT-safe constraints unchanged.

For deep daily waves and ULTRA prompts, use **`ultra-daily-improvement`** rule and `ULTRA-prompts.md` / `DAILY-IMPROVEMENT.md`.

## Ultra-scale continuous improvement (manager brief)

When the user asks for **suite-wide** or **daily recursive** polish, treat this rule + **`hap-multi-dashboard-scope`** as the contract: CEO-ready copy, policy clarity, OW-level visual discipline, smooth performance (**transform/opacity** for motion; passive scroll + rAF patterns in `340b.js`), and **cross-surface consistency**—implemented incrementally with human sign-off, not one-shot refactors of every file.
